==English==

===Etymology===
After its discoverer, Captain John Winter, vice-admiral to Sir Francis Drake.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Winter]]'s [[bark]]|?}}

# A tree ({{taxlink|Drimys winteri|species|noshow=1}}) native to [[Chile]] and [[Argentina]], grown as an [[ornamental]] plant for its reddish-brown bark, bright green, [[fragrant]] leaves and [[cluster]]s of [[creamy]] white, [[jasmine]]-[[scented]] flowers.
# The bark of this tree, formerly used medicinally.

